{"article_id":"dglefZL44WoI36e8","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"President Obama steps before the television cameras Tuesday morning","depth":5},{"id":1,"text":"to urge Republicans to avoid the automatic , across-the-board budget cuts","depth":6},{"id":2,"text":"scheduled to hit the government at the beginning of March ,","depth":6},{"id":3,"text":"according to a White House official .","depth":4},{"id":4,"text":"With Congress out of town this week","depth":6},{"id":5,"text":"and Mr. Obama back in Washington after a weekend golf vacation in Florida ,","depth":6},{"id":6,"text":"the president will press his case","depth":6},{"id":7,"text":"for passing more tax increases","depth":7},{"id":8,"text":"instead of relying solely on spending cuts","depth":9},{"id":9,"text":"as Republicans want","depth":9},{"id":10,"text":"in order to produce enough deficit reduction over the next 10 years","depth":9},{"id":11,"text":"to avoid the so-called sequester","depth":10},{"id":12,"text":"set to kick in March 1 .","depth":10},{"id":13,"text":"\" The president will make clear","depth":8},{"id":14,"text":"that we need to help the middle class get ahead","depth":9},{"id":15,"text":"and help our businesses create jobs , \"","depth":9},{"id":16,"text":"a White House official said Monday night .","depth":7},{"id":17,"text":"\" These cuts do just the opposite .","depth":6},{"id":18,"text":"But time and again , Republicans in Congress have said","depth":6},{"id":19,"text":"they would rather see these devastating cuts go into effect","depth":7},{"id":20,"text":"than close a single loophole","depth":8},{"id":21,"text":"that benefit the wealthy . \"","depth":8},{"id":22,"text":"Mr. Obama has invited emergency responders to join him on the stage","depth":6},{"id":23,"text":"to illustrate the types of jobs","depth":8},{"id":24,"text":"that are on the line","depth":8},{"id":25,"text":"if Congress fails to avoid the $ 85 billion in cuts","depth":8},{"id":26,"text":"divided between defense and domestic needs .","depth":8},{"id":27,"text":"If the cuts go into effect ,","depth":6},{"id":28,"text":"economists have warned","depth":7},{"id":29,"text":"that hundreds of thousands of middle-class jobs across the country could be lost .","depth":7},{"id":30,"text":"The White House said Monday","depth":5},{"id":31,"text":"that the Federal Emergency Management Agency would eliminate funding for state and local grants","depth":7},{"id":32,"text":"that support firefighter positions and state and local emergency management personnel ,","depth":7},{"id":33,"text":"hampering the government ' s ability","depth":7},{"id":34,"text":"to respond to natural disasters and other emergencies .","depth":7},{"id":35,"text":"Before Congress left for a weeklong recess ,","depth":4},{"id":36,"text":"defense-hawk Republicans furiously filed bills in the House and Senate","depth":5},{"id":37,"text":"to cancel the defense cuts","depth":6},{"id":38,"text":"and replace them with savings from attrition in the federal workforce .","depth":6},{"id":39,"text":"SEE ALSO :","depth":3},{"id":40,"text":"Sequestration becomes partisan game of political chicken on the Hill","depth":3},{"id":41,"text":"But other Republicans have said","depth":5},{"id":42,"text":"they are ready to swallow the defense cuts","depth":7},{"id":43,"text":"in order to get the domestic cuts ,","depth":7},{"id":44,"text":"and argue","depth":7},{"id":45,"text":"that the Defense Department has grown along with the rest of the government","depth":8},{"id":46,"text":"and can handle the trims .","depth":8},{"id":47,"text":"Mr. Obama and most Democrats don ' t want to see the domestic cuts","depth":5},{"id":48,"text":"and warn","depth":6},{"id":49,"text":"that slicing the budget so indiscriminately could send the still-struggling economic recovery off the rails .","depth":6},{"id":50,"text":"Republicans are still upset over agreeing to a deal on New Year ' s Day","depth":5},{"id":51,"text":"to avoid the first sequester deadline","depth":6},{"id":52,"text":"that relied on tax increases rather than cuts to entitlement programs .","depth":6},{"id":53,"text":"Mr. Obama has proposed a deficit-reduction plan","depth":7},{"id":54,"text":"he says","depth":9},{"id":55,"text":"is balanced","depth":9},{"id":56,"text":"because it increases taxes","depth":9},{"id":57,"text":"and overhauls entitlement programs ,","depth":9},{"id":58,"text":"though he has been very short on the specifics of the spending cuts .","depth":6},{"id":59,"text":"\" The House and Senate have said","depth":9},{"id":60,"text":"they want to do a budget ,","depth":9},{"id":61,"text":"and that budget must be balanced","depth":9},{"id":62,"text":"and cut spending","depth":11},{"id":63,"text":"where we can ,","depth":11},{"id":64,"text":"reform our entitlement programs","depth":11},{"id":65,"text":"and ask the wealthiest few and big corporations to pay their fair share , \"","depth":11},{"id":66,"text":"the official said .","depth":7},{"id":67,"text":"At the very least ,","depth":8},{"id":68,"text":"Mr. Obama argues ,","depth":8},{"id":69,"text":"Republicans should pass a short-term fix","depth":8},{"id":70,"text":"and punt the issue down the road","depth":9},{"id":71,"text":"to allow time for a thorough debate","depth":10},{"id":72,"text":"about overhauling the nation ' s tax code","depth":11},{"id":73,"text":"and closing tax loopholes .","depth":11}],"relations":[{"parent":147,"left":112,"right":146,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":112,"left":95,"right":111,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":95,"left":77,"right":94,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":77,"left":76,"right":3,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":76,"left":0,"right":75,"relation":"purpose","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":75,"left":1,"right":2,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":94,"left":85,"right":93,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":85,"left":78,"right":84,"relation":"context"